
Overview of verb beset

The verb beset has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (5) harass, hassle, harry, chivy, chivvy, chevy, chevvy, beset, plague, molest, provoke -- (annoy continually or chronically; "He is known to harry his staff when he is overworked"; "This man harasses his female co-workers")
2. (2) beset, set upon -- (assail or attack on all sides: "The zebra was beset by leopards")
3. encrust, incrust, beset -- (decorate or cover lavishly (as with gems))
